org.apache.hadoop.fs.s3a.commit.files

Class SuccessData

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.hadoop.fs.s3a.commit.files.PersistentCommitData
      • org.apache.hadoop.fs.s3a.commit.files.SuccessData
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    @InterfaceAudience.Private
 @InterfaceStability.Unstable
public class SuccessData
extends PersistentCommitData
    Summary data saved into a _SUCCESS marker file. This provides an easy way to determine which committer was used to commit work.
    1. File length == 0: classic FileOutputCommitter.
    2. Loadable as SuccessData: A s3guard committer with name in in committer field.
    3. Not loadable? Something else.
    This is an unstable structure intended for diagnostics and testing. Applications reading this data should use/check the name field to differentiate from any other JSON-based manifest and to identify changes in the output format.
    See Also:
